Claude CodeCursor / generic MCP client <p>Add to your project's <code>.mcp.json</code> or to user-level <code>~/.claude/mcp.json</code>:</p> <pre><code>{
  "mcpServers": {
    "lcp-requests": {
      "command": "lcp",
      "args": ["serve", "/absolute/path/to/requests.lcp.json"]
    }
  }
}
</code></pre> <p>Or use the CLI shortcut:</p> <pre><code>claude mcp add lcp-requests -- lcp serve /absolute/path/to/requests.lcp.json
</code></pre> <p>Most clients accept the same <code>mcpServers</code> shape. Point <code>command</code> to the <code>lcp</code> executable and pass <code>serve &lt;manifest&gt;</code> as the <code>args</code> array. Consult your client's documentation for the config file location.</p>

Claude CodeCursor / generic MCP client <pre><code># Add the universal server (resolves any library on demand)
claude mcp add lcp-universal -- lcp serve-all

# With registry fallback
claude mcp add lcp-universal -- lcp serve-all \
    --registry https://raw.githubusercontent.com/zazza123/lcp-registry/refs/heads/main
</code></pre> <p>Or edit <code>.mcp.json</code> manually:</p> <pre><code>{
  "mcpServers": {
    "lcp-universal": {
      "command": "lcp",
      "args": ["serve-all"]
    }
  }
}
</code></pre> <pre><code>{
  "mcpServers": {
    "lcp-universal": {
      "command": "lcp",
      "args": ["serve-all"]
    }
  }
}
</code></pre>
